<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0">
    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>The Acting Secretary of State to
                        the Embassy in Argentina</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1947v08</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d234</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">234</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1947-03-26T19:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1947-03-26T19:00:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-03-26T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-03-26T19:00:00-05:00" n="234" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d234">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">835.6363/3–1347: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Embassy in Argentina</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-03-26T19:00:00-05:00">March 26, 1947—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>226. <hi rend="italic">La Prensa</hi> Mar 6 reports five bills introduced Chamber
                    Deputies recommending ban on mixed companies,<note n="3" xml:id="d234fn1">Companies jointly operated or regulated by private firms and by the
                        state.</note> expropriation private oil <pb facs="0295" n="279" xml:id="pg_279"/> companies, and other restrictive measures. What in opinion
                    Embassy are motives, likelihood action and possible result.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
